history.content:
Please note: The deadline to submit a GSI application for Summer Session courses is April 15, 2017.

 

Online applications are located at:

https://willow.coe.berkeley.edu/PHP/gsiapp/menu.php

 

GSI positions are available for CS 10, 61A, 61BL, 61C, 70, 160, and 169. EE 16A is the only EE course offered this Summer Session.

 

Seniors who are graduating this semester must postpone their graduation to August to be eligible to be a GSI for the Summer Session.

 

If you are interested in becoming a GSI for the Summer Session 2017, you must meet the Graduate Division requirements.

 

If you are an international student and Summer Session 2017 will be your first time being a GSI, you must complete the Language Proficiency Screening Questionnaire.

 

If you have any questions please contact me.

 

Patrick Hernan

EECS GSI Coordinator
